flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Periodic review of inventory levels and supply chain performance.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Retrieve current inventory levels and demand forecasts from SAP S/4HANA.]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: AutoML - Analyze data to define optimal inventory targets and policies.]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Safety Stock Service - Optimize safety stock levels and buffer strategies using historical data.]
  N3 --> N4[Cortex: Remote Functions - Identify and plan strategies to reduce obsolete and excess inventory.]
  N4 --> N5{PB: CWB Lifecycle - Review and adjust build-to-order vs. build-to-stock balance.}
  N5 -->|Primary| N6[PB: Remote Functions - Integrate service parts inventory planning across the network.]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Near real-time policy-driven actions with measurable P&L impact.]
  N5 -->|High variability in supply chain data| B1[Increase buffer strategies and safety stock levels.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Improved resilience against supply chain disruptions.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N5 -->|Significant excess inventory identified| B2[Implement targeted promotions or markdowns to reduce excess inventory.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Reduced carrying costs and improved inventory turnover.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N5 -->|Low demand forecast accuracy| B3[Engage human review and adjustment of inventory targets.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Enhanced accuracy in inventory planning and reduced risk of stockouts.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]